# API Development Guidelines

## Route Structure
- Follow RESTful conventions
- Use HTTP methods appropriately (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)
- Group related routes in subdirectories

## Request/Response Handling
```typescript
export const GET = async (req: MedusaRequest, res: MedusaResponse) => {
  const { id } = req.params
  
  try {
    const result = await vendorService.retrieveVendor(id)
    res.json({ vendor: result })
  } catch (error) {
    res.status(404).json({ error: "Vendor not found" })
  }
}
```

## Authentication & Authorization
- Use Medusa's built-in auth middleware
- Validate user permissions for vendor operations
- Check vendor ownership for sensitive operations

## Error Handling
- Return appropriate HTTP status codes
- Provide meaningful error messages
- Log errors for debugging (avoid exposing sensitive data)

## Input Validation
- Validate request parameters and body
- Use Zod schemas for complex validation
- Sanitize user inputs

## CORS Configuration
- Respect CORS settings from [medusa-config.ts](mdc:medusa-config.ts)
- Use environment-specific origins
- Handle preflight requests properly

## Rate Limiting
- Implement rate limiting for public endpoints
- Especially for report creation and vendor registration
- Use Redis for distributed rate limiting

## API Documentation
- Document endpoints with clear parameter descriptions
- Include example requests/responses
- Maintain API versioning strategy

## Security Considerations
- Validate file uploads (images for pets)
- Sanitize HTML content in descriptions
- Implement CSRF protection where needed
- Use HTTPS in production